palette = c("#B2182B", "#D6604D", "#F4A582", "#FDDBC7", "#D1E5F0", "#92C5DE", "#4393C3", "#2166AC")
palette_alt = numeric(length(palette))
for (i in 1:length(palette)) {if (i %% 2 == 1) {palette_alt[i] <- palette[(i + 1) %/% 2]} 
                              else {palette_alt[i] <- palette[length(palette) - (i - 1) %/% 2]}}

gghistogram_style = function () {geom_histogram(bins = 60, alpha = 0.75)}
ggdensity_style = function () {geom_density(colour = "white", alpha = 0.75)}

ggscatter_style_def = function () {geom_point(size = 1.5, shape = 16, alpha = 0.75)}
ggscatter_style = function () {geom_point(colour = "#2166AC", size = 1.5, shape = 16, alpha = 0.75)}

gglabel_style = function () {geom_text(vjust = -0.5)}

ggqqplot_style = function () {geom_qq(colour = "#2166AC", size = 1.5, shape = 16, alpha = 0.75)}
ggqqline_style = function () {geom_qq_line(linetype = "dashed", linewidth = 1.1, color = "#B2182B")}

gghline_style = function (x) {geom_hline(yintercept = x, linetype = "dashed", linewidth = 1.1, color = "#B2182B")}

gginterval_confidence = function (model) {
  geom_ribbon(aes(ymin = predict(model, interval = "confidence")[, 2],
      ymax = predict(model, interval = "confidence")[, 3]),
    color = "#B2182B", fill = "#B2182B", alpha = 0.2)
}

gginterval_prediction = function (model) {
  geom_ribbon(aes(ymin = predict(model, interval = "prediction")[, 2],
      ymax = predict(model, interval = "prediction")[, 3]),
    color = "#FDDBC7", fill = "#FDDBC7", alpha = 0.2)
}

Define animation function

animate = function (dataframes, func) {
  saveGIF({
      for (name in names(dataframes))
        print(func(name, dataframes[[name]]))
    },
    movie.name = paste(deparse(substitute(func)), ".gif"),
    interval = 0.1, ani.width = 600, ani.height = 400)
}

Data Ingestion

Load files

all_path = "D:\\Data Extraction\\all-crypto-daily"
cat_path = "D:\\Data Extraction\\categories-daily"

all_file = list.files(all_path, pattern = "*.csv", full.names = TRUE)
cat_file = list.files(cat_path, pattern = "artificial*", full.names = TRUE)

get_date = function (string) {
  regex = "([0-9]{4}-[0-9]{2}-[0-9]{2})"
  date = str_extract(string, regex)
  return (date)
}

read_df = function (file_list) {
  data_dict = list()
  for (file in file_list) {
    date = get_date(file)
    df = read.csv(file)

    df$MarketCap = as.numeric(gsub(",", "", df$MarketCap))
    df$Volume24h = as.numeric(gsub(",", "", df$Volume24h))
    df = df[!is.na(df$MarketCap), ]
    df = df[!is.na(df$Volume24h), ]
    df = df[!df$MarketCap == 0, ]
    df = df[!df$Volume24h == 0, ]

    date = substr(file, nchar(file) - 22, nchar(file) - 13)
    df[["Ratio"]] = df$Volume24h / df$MarketCap

    data_dict[[date]] = df
  }
  return (data_dict)
}

all_df = read_df(all_file)
cat_df = read_df(cat_file)
df = all_df[[1]]

Merge using date

join_df = function (all_df, cat_df) {
  df_joint = list()
  for (date in names(all_df)) {
    if (date %in% names(cat_df)) {
      df_A = all_df[[date]]
      df_B = cat_df[[date]]
      df_joint[[date]] = list(df_A, df_B)
    }
  }
  return (df_joint)
}

double_dataframes = join_df(all_df, cat_df)

Label data with categories

label_df = function (df1, df2, cat) {
  for (i in 1: nrow(df1)) {
    name = df1[i, "Name"]
    if (name %in% df2$Name) {df1[i, "Category"] = cat} 
    else {df1[i, "Category"] = "Others"}
  }
  return (df1)
}

dataframes = list()

for (date in names(double_dataframes)) {
  df1 = double_dataframes[[date]][[1]]
  df2 = double_dataframes[[date]][[2]]
  df = label_df(df1, df2, "AI")
  df = df[order(df$Category, decreasing = TRUE), ]
  dataframes[[date]] = df
}

plot_Mvol = function (date, df) {
  histogram =
    ggplot(df, aes(x = df$Volume24h, fill = Category)) + scale_color_manual(values = palette_alt) + gghistogram_style() + 
    scale_x_continuous(limits = c(1e-6, 1e11), name = "Logarithmic 24h Trading Volume (USD)", trans = 'log10') +
    scale_y_continuous(limits = c(0, 400), name = "Token Counts") +
    ggtitle(paste("Mass Distribution of Trading Volume", date))
  return (histogram)
}

plot_Dvol = function (date, df) {

    scale_y_continuous(limits = c(0, 0.4), name = "Token Counts") +

Logarithmic scatterplot

plot_scatter = function (date, df) {
  scatterplot =
    ggplot(df, aes(x = Volume24h, y = MarketCap, color = Category)) + 
    theme(legend.position = "none") + scale_color_manual(values = palette_alt) + ggscatter_style_def() +
    scale_x_continuous(trans = 'log10', limits = c(1e-6, 1e11), name = "Logarithmic 24h Trading Volume (USD)") +
    scale_y_continuous(trans = 'log10', limits = c(1, 1e13), name = "Logarithmic Market Capitalization (USD)") +
    ggtitle(paste("Logarithmic Relationship Scatterplot (Unlabelled)", date))
  return (scatterplot)
}

plot_scatter_label = function (date, df) {
  scatterplot =
    ggplot(df, aes(x = Volume24h, y = MarketCap, color = Category, label = Symbol)) + 
    theme(legend.position = "none") + scale_color_manual(values = palette_alt) + ggscatter_style_def() + gglabel_style() + 
    scale_x_continuous(trans = 'log10', limits = c(1e-6, 1e11), name = "Logarithmic 24h Trading Volume (USD)") +
    scale_y_continuous(trans = 'log10', limits = c(1, 1e13), name = "Logarithmic Market Capitalization (USD)") +
    ggtitle(paste("Logarithmic Relationship Scatterplot (Labelled)", date))
  return (scatterplot)
}

Data Transforming & Cleaning

Perform logarithmic transformation

log_transform = function (df) {
  logdf = df[, c("Symbol", "Name", "Category")]
  logdf$Volume24h_log = log10(df$Volume24h)
  logdf$MarketCap_log = log10(df$MarketCap)
  logdf = logdf[complete.cases(logdf), ]
  return (logdf)
}

logdf = log_transform(df)

Perform DBSCAN to identify outliers

dbscan_clean = function (df, selection) {
  dbscan_subset = df[, c("Volume24h_log", "MarketCap_log")]
  dbscan_subset = dbscan_subset[complete.cases(dbscan_subset), ]

  dbscan_result = dbscan(dbscan_subset, eps = 0.75, MinPts = 10)
  df$Cluster = factor(dbscan_result$cluster)
  df_clean = df[df$Cluster == 1, ]

  if (selection == "original") {return (df)} 
  else {return (df_clean)}
}

logdf = dbscan_clean(logdf, "original")
logdf_clean = dbscan_clean(logdf, "cleaned")

dataframes_pre = list()
dataframes_pos = list()

for (name in names(dataframes)) {
  df = log_transform(dataframes[[name]])
  df1 = dbscan_clean(df, "original")
  df2 = dbscan_clean(df, "cleaned")
  dataframes_pre[[name]] = df1
  dataframes_pos[[name]] = df2
}

DBSCAN result scatterplot

plot_cluster_pre = function (date, df) {
  clusterplot =
    ggplot(df, aes(x = Volume24h_log, y = MarketCap_log, color = Cluster, label = Symbol)) +

    scale_y_continuous(limits = c(-5, 12), name = "Logarithmic Market Capitalization (USD)") +
    ggtitle(paste("DBSCAN Clustering Result", date))
  return (clusterplot)
}

plot_cluster_pos = function (date, df) {

Regression Analysis

QQ-plot and residue plot

plot_qq = function (date, df) {
  model = lm(MarketCap_log~Volume24h_log, data = df)
  r = rstandard(model)

  qqplot =
    ggplot(df, aes(sample = r)) + ggqqplot_style() + ggqqline_style() + 
    scale_x_continuous(limits = c(-4, 4), name = "Theoretical Quantiles") +
    scale_y_continuous(limits = c(-5, 5), name = "Sample Quantiles") +
    ggtitle(paste("Quantile-Quantile Plot of Logarithmic Trading Volume", date))
  return (qqplot)
}

plot_res = function (date, df) {
  model = lm(MarketCap_log~Volume24h_log, data = df)
  hii = hatvalues(model)
  r = rstandard(model)

  residueplot =
    ggplot(df, aes(x = Volume24h_log, y = r)) + ggscatter_style() + gghline_style(-2) + gghline_style(2) +
    scale_x_continuous(limits = c(-5, 11), name = "Logarithmic 24h Trading Volume (USD)") +
    scale_y_continuous(limits = c(-5, 5), name = "Residue (Market Capitalization)") +
    ggtitle(paste("Standard Residue Plot of Logarithmic Trading Volume", date))
  return (residueplot)
}

grid.arrange(plot_qq("", logdf_clean), plot_res("", logdf_clean), nrow = 1)

Confidence and prediction intervals

plot_CI = function (date, df) {
  model = lm(MarketCap_log~Volume24h_log, data = df)
  CIplot =
    ggplot(df, aes(x = Volume24h_log, y = MarketCap_log)) +
    ggscatter_style() + gginterval_confidence(model) + gginterval_prediction(model) +
    scale_x_continuous(limits = c(-5, 11), name = "Logarithmic 24h Trading Volume (USD)") +
    scale_y_continuous(limits = c(-5, 12), name = "Logarithmic Market Capitalization (USD)") +
    ggtitle(paste("Scatterplot with Confidence Interval", date))
  return (CIplot)
}

plot_CI("", logdf_clean)
